<br />Yeah it was either in late '96 or mid '97 when I first put the html together, and had it up on Geocities.  I had a separate NES ROM site on there too, where I'd post requested ROMs, heheh. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />  (holy crap, <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/19991010210344/http://www.geocities.com/Athens/Olympus/2077/roms.htm" class="postlink">it's archived</a>.)  Best thing on there was the 24hour.txt ROM warning I stole from a Usenet post.
